                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="acronym_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" hclass="sensetop" htag="span"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a word formed from the first letters of the words that make up the name of something, for example ‘AIDS’ is an <span class="dh">acronym</span> for ‘acquired immune deficiency syndrome’</span></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" id="acronym_unbox_1" unbox="wordorigin"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">1940s: from Greek <span class="ei">akron</span> ‘end, tip’ + <span class="ei">-onym</span>.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
